Description: Fragment of lip, neck and double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown; no slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 57. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0153)
